phrases: We are about to enter Tokyo airspace.
Three minutes until the drop point.
Open the hatch.
This route can only be used once.
There are no second chances.
Got that?
That is supposed to be Tokyo?
You want us to break your granddaughter out?
Yes.
The leader of the Ming Hua Group,
the largest conglomerate in Shanghai,
is in love with her.
He says that, in exchange for her,
he will negotiate with the Association of Asian Nations on my behalf.
In other words, you are talking about a marriage of convenience?
I never imagined this day would come.
To think I would witness first-hand
what it is like when a nation declines.
I will secure the escape route.
We will meet up in 36 hours.
Good luck!
Thanks!
The reality of the destruction around us fills our mind
The raging rain sounds like a storm of tears
that your eyes were given to you to acknowledge others,
that your eyes were given to you to acknowledge others,
that your eyes were given to you to acknowledge others,
that your eyes were given to you to acknowledge others,
that your eyes were given to you to acknowledge others,
that your voice was given to you to tell others how you feel
All living things
bear witness to my song
Your heart contains all its truth
Even when all you see in your path are storms
remember that your strength is no coincidence
Man, Tokyo's changed a lot in such a short time...
Kn-Knock it off!
We are the ones who found this!
Stay back!
They are stealing vaccines from each other?
That is... a Void?!
We are looking for new recruits for a certain project.
If you swear your allegiance to President Ou ma,
we will grant you the right to live.
President Ouma...?
They are a Secret Service!
Why?!
Shall we do her, Nanba?
Her Void's bound to be trash anyway.
Agreed.
That is far enough, cake-eaters.
Do not go showing off by using a girl who does not even know how to disengage the safety!
An enemy?
Hold on, Miyabi.
That emblem...
Could he be a member of the Undertakers?
What if I am?
You mean...
The one running this school right now is Shu?
I cannot believe this... he is just Shu.
That was rude.
Now, now.
Sorry.
She pretty much idolizes the president.
Idolizes...?
Secret Service members Takarada Ritsu and Herikawa Miyabi.
We have brought a guest.
What does the Resonance Gauge say?
Her number's higher than you would think.
I see.
This one might be a good find, Shu.
Shu?!
I cannot draw out her Void like that.
Make her look at me.
Congratulations.
You are Rank A.
I want you to work hard for this school.
Rank... A?
Me?
Hey, Shu!
Ah.
It is been a long time, Argo.
I am glad you are all right.
This is a pretty elaborate setup you have here.
There is a possibility the government is introducing a new genomic weapon.
Genomic weapon?
Yes.
One of the students fell victim to it a few days ago.
By the way...
Was not the student council president a girl named Arisa Kuhouin?
Do you have business with her?
I am under orders from her grandfather to bring her back outside.
So, where is she?
I am sorry, but Shu has a full schedule.
Can we walk and talk?
Sure, fine by me.
What are they doing?
Look.
It is an army transport ship abandoned during the confusion resulting from the sealing of Tokyo.
It has vaccine and ammunition inside.
And you are scavenging them.
Pretty miserly...
Whoa, hey!
They are all symptomatic!
These parts will not hold out.
Work something out.
It is okay.
If they do their work, they can get injections before they hit Stage II.
That is...!
Squad leader.
Yes, Sir!
You are not fulfilling your quota.
I would like to know why.
I am afraid that the symptomatic students are not able to work at their max
We have got trouble!
It is pump 12!
Whose is it?!
Tamadate Souta, from 2-A!
Do we have a spare?
No, they are all in use!
No choice, then.
We have that medical oxygen tank we salvaged, right?
Get that.
Wait.
His diving suit should have a small emergency tank, am I right?
If he uses that, he should be able to cut the hose and escape.
There is a switch on the helmet.
He has to figure it out for himself.
So do not interfere.
What?!
You are just going to let him die?!
You are scum!
Hurry up and help him!
We cannot go around wasting resources on a Rank F.
What was that, little Void Prince?!
Do not come any closer.
Do you understand the situation?
If Shu becomes symptomatic, it is all over.
Hey, cut the bullshit, Shu!
Argo!
You are going to ignore my orders?!
Damn straight, you dumbass!
You are just Shu, so do not order me around like some big-shot!
Argo...
We are currently planning an escape from Tokyo.
To do that, we need everyone to work together toward the goal.
There are no exceptions.
What about these guys, then?
Why are you discriminating against them?
We are distinguishing.
Under these circumstances, we cannot afford to be egalitarian.
And we will not be handing over Kuhouin.
She has an exceptional Void.
Not to mention, there is no way we would let one person escape alone.
Please swear obedience to me.
Or else...
Do what you want.
The way you are now, I would die of the cancer before I ever obeyed you.
Restrain him.
Yes, Sir.
Inori, you have switched to doing whatever Shu wants now?
No.
This was my choice.
Put a watch on Kuhouin, just in case.
Yes, Sir.
Damn, he pisses me off!
Who the hell does Shu think he is?!
Acting like an arrogant little shit...
There was a girl who died.
That you, Tsugumi?
Aye.
Long time no see, Argo.
I would heard that you joined up with Tennozu, but...
Is Ayase with you?
Nay.
The moment Aya heard that you would been captured...
What do you think you are doing?
The rules say that is what happens when someone disobeys my orders.
It would set a bad example if I made an exception just because he used to be one of my own.
I get that you are hurting because Hare died, but what you have done is just...
You get it?
You read people's hearts that easily, huh?
I am glad no one else is around.
If anyone had seen that,
I would have had to punish you, Rank S or not.
He is totally messed up.
Why is everyone going along with this?
To put it simply, it is fear.
The stress from the red line steadily closing in,
fear of the Apocalypse Virus,
and the rampant violence and looting...
Against that backdrop, the power of the Voids is just too clear-cut.
When Shu decided to become king, it took less than a second.
A kingdom by the Voids and for the Voids...
That is what this school is right now.
Damn it!
Hey, Mana...
She is collecting your shards with all he is got right now.
It looks like he is finally started to fulfill his potential.
It is not enough, though.
More...
We have to keep up the pressure.
It is going according to plan, then.
As the line advances, it appears many youth are joining forces with Tennozu.
They are collecting Voids, are not they?
First, you surprised me with the Ghost unit, and now this.
Your motherly love is quite harsh, is not it, Dr. Ouma?
I am only doing what is necessary,
as the one carrying out his...
Kurosu's wishes.
You are still here?
Address any complaints to the Void Prince, please.
I heard a member of the Undertakers was captured.
I believe that I have the right to interview him.
The prince is nervous about what you are up to.
If you get too meddlesome, you will be taken down for real.
But I can protect you.
Never underestimate a Kuhouin.
Hey, Yahiro...
Did Hare really die because of a new weapon?
Yes.
Why do you ask?
There is a rumor.
They are saying maybe Hare died because her Void was...
Watch what you say.
If you hear anyone spreading those lies, you tell me.
Got it?
What should I do, Hare?
Everyone is changing!
I suppose to everyone else, I look like a selfish tyrant.
Does it hurt?
It is not like I am doing this to be popular.
It is to get everyone safely out of Tokyo.
That is why I cannot stop.
Or else Hare will have...
She will have died for nothing.
All I need is you, Inori.
As long as you are here with me...
You really want me?
Shu?
I am sorry, Sir!
The member of the Undertakers we had in custody has escaped!
Can I assume Arisa's in her dorm?
Well, she normally is.
But if you are going to make a move, tell me first!
To fool your enemies, you must first fool your allies.
What is the point of tricking us?!
Things are a mess here thanks to you!
Bear with me, Aya!
If you get carried away and rush out there now, you will just get captured by the Secret Service.
Samukawa to the Secret Service.
The prisoner's on the loose.
Capture him AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.
You two search the area around Schoolhouse 2.
Yes, Sir!
Inori, you look for Kuhouin.
Argo might make contact with her.
You...
You joined the Secret Service?
He ran toward the gym!
Follow me!
Yes, Sir!
That is far enough, Argo!
You are a cornered rat.
Give up and surrender.
Well, well.
For a second there I thought you had guys showing yourself,
but you brought Voids for insurance.
Maybe you think wearing that thing makes you like Gai,
but you are not even close, you poser!
We will fight one-on-one.
If you lose, your little King act...
ends here and now!
Too bad, Void Prince!
Argo!
How the hell did you wind up like this?
We really liked that pale-faced weakling struggling with all his might thing you had going!
You try doing this, then.
If you think there is some other way to keep everyone safe in this situation, then tell me!
Get away from Shu!
You?
I am not as soft as Shu.
Surrender!
Now!
No way...
This cannot be...
Stop it...
I do not...
This is Samukawa.
Secure a perimeter around the gym and arrest anyone within 30 meters, regardless of rank.
This gym is to be sealed off, effective immediately.
Yahiro...
There was nothing wrong with that girl,
but she died anyway.
Was it because her Void broke?
We cannot know that for sure.
I am certain of it!
You lied to me.
You told me a genomic weapon killed Hare.
What now?
A kingdom centered around Voids lives side by side with death!
There is no going back now.
I knew you would hesitate to use Voids if you found out.
But if our current system collapses, all of us will end up dead.
We have to keep going.
We have to keep the truth from everyone until we begin our operation.
Got it?
What the hell are you saying?!
Stop using Voids right now!
If you start a war like this, you have no idea how many will die!
Do not listen to him, he is crazy!
Come on, open your eyes!
You are right...
Shu!
Shu
If I break this, Argo will die.
I have to tell everyone as soon as possible!
I cannot believe Voids are...
I found you.
You...
You did not hold up your end.
I assume we can forget about the deal.
I suppose there is no choice.
Please leave Japan as soon as you can.
There is trouble brewing on the Pacific.
It is finally time, then.
I doubt Shu'll ever forgive me for this.
